comment: Terminator Dark Fate suffers from what I call the Godfather Part 3 syndrome. That is you got a sequel which is better then the first film which is followed up by a mediocre third installment. Yes Dark Fate is the best sequel to T2 and it has it's awesome moments but it also has its flaws. Now if you look at the Rocky franchise from Rocky to Rocky IV each film got better and better then came Rocky V which is the worst in the franchise. But why did each Rocky to Rocky IV get better? Stallone created memorable characters and built upon the nostalgia. Rocky Balboa continues the trend....rarely has a franchise gotten better and unlike Dark Fate (Rocky III) is awesome thanks to Mr T. Once again Stallone created a memorable and cast the right actor. And he turns things on there head by having Apollo Creed train Rocky for his rematch. Stallone added something new. He also killed of Mickey which was a shock at the time. And with Rocky Balboa Stallone connected with a modern cinema audience something Arnold Schwarzenegger has failed to do. If the terminator franchise is to continue it needs a writer and director who are not fans of the terminator films and a new actor playing the terminator. The Rock or Vin Diesel being everyone's choice
